\id JAS Kapingamarangi 
\h James 
\toc1 Di Lede a James 
\toc2 James 
\toc3 James 
\mt1 JAMES  
\mt2 Di Lede a James  
\imt1 Di haga modongoohia:  
\im \bk Di lede a James\bk* la nia agoago hagamaamaa o nia mouli nia daangada, ne hihi ang gi nia dama a God huogodoo ala e noho i nia madagowaa huogodoo i henuailala. James e hai hegau gi nia helekai hagatautau e logo belee haga modongoohia gi nia daangada huogodoo di hai o di kabemee, gei e dagi nia hagamamaanadu mo nia mouli o nia dama a Christ i ana agoago nia mee aanei: di hai o di maluagina mo di hagaloale, nia hagamada, nia hangaahai humalia, hilihili dangada, hagadonu mono hegau, hai hegau gi tolole, kabemee, lagamaaloo, hagamuamua mo di hila gi lala, hagi aga digau ala i golo, hagaamu ia, manawa hagakono, mo talodalo.  
\ip Di lede deenei e haga modongoohia aga nia hagalabagau o nia hegau o digau ala e hagadonu a Christ.  
\iot Di hagahonu di beebaa deenei:  
\io1 Di haga modongoohia \ior (1.1)\ior*  
\io1 Di hagadonu mo di iloo mee \ior (1.2-8)\ior*  
\io1 Di hagaloale mo di maluagina \ior (1.9-11)\ior*  
\io1 Di hagadina mo di hagahuaidu \ior (1.12-18)\ior*  
\io1 Di hagalongo mo di hagagila aga nnelekai \ior (1.19-27)\ior*  
\io1 Di hilihili dangada \ior (2.1-13)\ior*  
\io1 Di hagadonu mono hegau \ior (2.14-26)\ior*  
\io1 Tama a Christ mo dono holole \ior (3.1-18)\ior*  
\io1 Tama a Christ mo henuailala \ior (4.1-6)\ior*  
\io1 Hagadilinga agoago \ior (5.7-20)\ior*  
\c 1  
\p
\v 1 Mai James, tangada hai hegau a God, mo Tagi go Jesus Christ.  
\p Taga aloho ang gi nia dama a God huogodoo ala gu modoho i henuailala.\x * \xo 1.1 \xt Matthew 13.55; Mark 6.3; Acts 15.13; Galatians 1.19\x*   
\s1 Di hagadonu mo di iloo mee  
\p
\v 2 Ogu duaahina nei, goodou gi maanadua bolo goodou e haadanga lamalia gi nia hagadilinga haingadaa huogodoo ala ma ga tale adu gi goodou.  
\v 3 Idimaa, goodou e iloo bolo godou hagadonu ma ga maaloo i nia haingadaa aanei, le e haga llauehe aga godou manawa hagakono i di madagoaa haingadaa.  
\v 4 Goodou la gii pula i godou manawa hagakono i nia madagoaa haingadaa gii noho hua beelaa, gei goodou gaa dohu huoloo, ga dogomaalia.  
\v 5 Maa tangada i goodou e dee dohu dono iloo mee, geia gi dalodalo ang gi God, ge God ga dugu anga, idimaa, God e manawa dumaalia gaa hana hua beelaa ang gi nia daangada huogodoo.  
\v 6 Malaa, goodou e hai loo gi dalodalo mo di hagadonu, hagalee manawa logo. Tangada dela e manawa logo le e hai gadoo be di beau o di moana dela e bagibagia i di madangi.  
\v 7-8 Tagadilinga dangada beenei digi dogomaalia dono hilihili, digi hagatogomaalia ana mee e hai, ia gi hudee maanadu bolo ia e mee di kae ana mee mai baahi o Dimaadua.   
\s1 Di hagaloale mo di maluagina  
\p
\v 9 Nia duaahina dama a Christ hagaloale e hai loo gi tenetene i di madagoaa digaula e haga menege aga go God.  
\v 10 Nia duaahina dama a Christ maluagina gi tenetene labelaa i di madagoaa dela e dugu eia go God, idimaa, digau ala e maluagina ga hagalee, gadoo be di akai o di laagau geinga.\x * \xo 1.10 \xt Isaiah 40.6-7 \x*  
\v 11 Gei di laa gaa hobo, ga welengina, gaa dudu nia laagau, gei nia akai gaa mae, ga monnono. Nadau madamada ga hagalee. Dela gadoo be tangada maluagina dela ma ga daaligi ga hagalee i dono madagoaa e hai dana moomee.   
\s1 Nia hagamada  
\p
\v 12 E maluagina go tangada dela e manawa dahi i lodo nia hagamada haingadaa. I muli di aali i ono hagamada, geia e kae di hui o di mouli. Deenei go di mouli a God ne hagababa ang gi digau ala e aloho i de Ia.  
\v 13 Maa tangada gaa tale gi nia hagamada haingadaa, geia gi hudee helekai boloo, “Nia hagamada aanei ne loomoi i baahi o God.” Idimaa, di huaidu e deemee di hagamada a God, gei God hogi hagalee e hagamada tangada.  
\v 14 Malaa, tangada le e tale gi nia hagamada mai i ono hiihai huaidu.  
\v 15 Gei ono hiihai huaidu ga hagadili aga nia huaidu, gei di huaidu ga tomo aga gaa hidi ai di made.   
\p
\v 16 Ogu ihoo hagaaloho nei, hudee heia goodou gi halahalau ina go tangada.  
\v 17 Nia wanga dehuia humalia huogodoo, mono maluagina e dohu huogodoo, le e lloomoi i di langi i baahi o God dela ne hai nia maahina o di langi. God hagalee huli, ge hagalee hagabouli.\x * \xo 1.17 \xt 1-Samuel 15.29\x*  
\v 18 Mai dono hiihai oono, Mee ne hai gidaadou mai ana helekai donu, bolo gii hai gidaadou nia ulu mmaadua o ana mee huogodoo.   
\s1 Hagalongo mo di haga gila  
\p
\v 19 Ogu duaahina hagaaloho nei, goodou gi langahia di mee deenei: Tangada nei mo tangada nei i goodou huogodoo, gi limalima di hagalongo, malaa, hudee hagalellele di helekai, hudee limalima di hagawelewele.  
\v 20 Idimaa, di hagawelewele o tangada la hagalee hagamaamaa di haga gila aga di manawa donu a God.  
\v 21 Malaa, goodou haga mogowaa ina goodou gi daha mo nia hangaahai milimilia, mo nia haihai hala huogodoo. Goodou dugu anga goodou gi God ge gi kae ina ana helekai ala e dogi go Mee gi lodo godou manawa, aanei nia helekai e mee di haga mouli goodou.   
\p
\v 22 Goodou haga hai hegau ina nnelekai a God. Maa goodou ga hagalongo hua gi nia maa, gei goodou e bida halahalau hua goodou.  
\v 23 Tangada dela ma ga hagalongo hua gi nia helekai a God, gei hagalee haga gila aga nia maa, ia e hai gadoo be tangada dela ma gaa mmada gi lodo di kalaadi, ia ne mmada hua gi dono ada.  
\v 24 Mee e mmada gi humalia gi dono ada. Dono madagoaa ne hana gi daha mo di kalaadi, geia gu limalima hua gu de langahia dono ada.  
\v 25 Tangada dela e mmada gii donu gi taganoho hai donu dogomaalia dela e haga dagaloaha nia daangada, ga hagalongo gii donu, geia hagalee hagalongo hua ga de langahia di maa, gei mee e daudali ai, deenei tangada a God e hagahumalia i ana mee huogodoo ala e hai.   
\p
\v 26 Maa tangada i golo e hagamaanadu bolo ia tangada daumaha humalia, geia e deemee di benebene dono holole, dono hai daumaha le e balumee hua, ia e bida halahalau hua ia.  
\v 27 Di mee a God Tamana dela e hai bolo taumaha dela e madammaa gei e donu, la deenei: Madamada humalia nia damagiigi ala guu mmade nadau maadua, mo nia ahina guu mmade nadau lodo i nadau haingadaa, ge hudee hagahuaidu ina ginaadou gi nia hangaahai huaidu o henuailala.   
\c 2  
\s1 Hudee hilihili dangada  
\p
\v 1 Ogu duaahina nei, i di godou hagadonu tadau Dagi madamada go Jesus Christ, goodou hudee dugudugu gee nia daangada i di gili nadau hangaahai.  
\v 2 Dolomaa taane maluagina dono buulei goolo, e ulu ono gahu humalia, ga ulu mai gi godou baahi i di miiting, gei taane hagaloale e ulu i nia gahu huaidu e ulu mai labelaa,  
\v 3 maa goodou ga hagalabagau taane ono goloo humalia, ga helekai gi mee, “Noho i hongo di lohongo humalia deenei,” ga helekai gi tangada ono goloo huaidu boloo, “Duu i gono,” be, “Noho gi hongo di baba i baahi ogu wae,”  
\v 4 malaa, goodou gu ihala i di godou waewae godou mehanga, ga hidi mai dau hilihili nia maanadu huaidu!   
\p
\v 5 Ogu duaahina hagaaloho nei, goodou hagalongo! God e hilihili digau hagaloale o henuailala bolo gii honu i di hagadonu, gi hai mee gi Tenua dela ne hagababa ang gi digau ala e aloho i de Ia.  
\v 6 Gei goodou la gu haga balumee digau ala e hagaloale! Ma koai ala e wanga goodou gi di haingadaa, gi di gowaa hai gabunga? Go digau ala e maluagina!  
\v 7 Aanei go digau ala e helekai huaidu i di ingoo humalia dela ne gowadu gi goodou.   
\p
\v 8 Goodou gaa hai di mee dela e donu maa goodou ga hagalongo gi taganoho o tenua o God, dela guu hihi gi lodo di Beebaa Dabu,  
\q1 “Aloho i tangada dela i do baahi,  
\q1 gii hai be do aloho i di goe.”\x * \xo 2.8  \xt Leviticus 19.18\x*   
\m
\v 9 Maa goodou ga dugudugu gee nia daangada mai i nia hangaahai digaula, malaa, goodou guu hai di huaidu, gei nnaganoho gaa hai bolo goodou digau gu dagadagahi nnaganoho.  
\v 10 Tangada dela ma ga dagahi dana haganoho e dahi i nia haganoho, geia gu dagahi nia haganoho huogodoo.  
\v 11 Idimaa, go tangada lahua ne helekai boloo,  
\q1 “Hudee hai be di manu,”  
\m geia ne helekai labelaa boloo,  
\q1 “Goe hudee daaligidia tangada gii made.”  
\m Ma e aha maa goe hagalee hai be di manu, gei goe ne daaligi tangada gii made, malaa, goe tangada gu dagadagahi nnaganoho.\x * \xo 2.11  \xt Exodus 20.13,14; Deuteronomy 5.17,18\x*  
\v 12 Helekai gei gi mouli be nia daangada ala ga hagi aga go taganoho e haga dagaloaha gidaadou.  
\v 13 Idimaa, God ga hagalee dumaalia ang gi tangada dela digi dumaalia gi dono ihoo, gei tumaalia le koia e mahi i di hagi aga.   
\s1 Di hagadonu mono hegau  
\p
\v 14 Ogu duaahina nei, dehee tahidamee o tangada dela e helekai bolo ia dono hagadonu i golo, gei ono hegau ai? E hai behee: tagadilinga hagadonu beenei e mee di haga mouli ia?  
\v 15 Dolomaa tadau duaahina daane be ahina i golo nadau gahu ai, mo nadau meegai hagalee dohu,  
\v 16 dehee tadinga o di godou helekai gi mee boloo, “E humalia. God ga hagahumalia laa goe! Gahu ina goe gi mahana, miami!” gei goodou digi wanga gi mee nia hagahumalia a mee?  
\v 17 Di hagadonu dela deai ono hegau ai, e modongoohia bolo di hagadonu hua e made.   
\p
\v 18 Dolomaa tangada ga helekai boloo, “Goe do hagadonu i golo, gei au agu hegau i golo.” Malaa, gei au ga helekai boloo, “Haga modongoohia ina mai gi di au tangada e hagadonu gei ono hegau ai, gei au ga haga modongoohia adu gi di goe dogu hagadonu mai i agu hegau.”  
\v 19 E hai behee go do hagadonu: Goe e hagadonu bolo God le e dahi hua? E humalia! Nia hagataalunga huaidu le e hagadonu labelaa beenei, gei e bolebole i nadau mmaadagu i God.  
\v 20 Goe tangada dadaulia! Goe e hiihai bolo ma gi haga modongoohia ina adu gi di goe bolo di hagadonu dela ono hegau ai, la dono hadinga ai?  
\v 21 Tadau damana go Abraham la ne aha gaa donu i baahi o God? Mee ne donu i baahi o God mai dana hai dela ne tigidaumaha dana dama daane go Isaac i hongo di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha.\x * \xo 2.21  \xt Genesis 22.1-14\x*  
\v 22 Goe digi modongoohia? Dono hagadonu mo dono hai hegau ne ngalua ngaadahi, bolo gii dohu ai dono hagadonu mai i ana hegau.  
\v 23 Deelaa laa, nia helekai di Beebaa Dabu la gu kila aga, ala e helekai boloo,  
\q1 “Abraham la gu hagadonu a God.  
\q1 Idimaa go dono hagadonu,  
\q1 God guu hila ang gi mee gii donu a mee  
\q1 i dono baahi.”  
\m God gu haga ingoo Abraham bolo di hoo hagaaloho ni oono.\x * \xo 2.23  \xt Genesis 15.6; 2-Chronicles 20.7; Isaiah 41.8\x*  
\v 24 Goodou gi modongoohia bolo tangada le e donu i baahi o God mai i ana hegau, mo dono hagadonu, hagalee mai i dono hagadonu lahua.  
\v 25 E hai labelaa be di ahina huaidu go Rahab. Mee ne donu i baahi o God i dana hai dela ne benebene digau hagadina o Israel, ge ne hagau digaula hagammuni i tuai ala.\x * \xo 2.25  \xt Joshua 2.1-21; Hebrews 11.21\x*  
\v 26 Tuaidina dela dono hagataalunga ai, tuaidina hua e made, gei di hagadonu dela ono hegau ai, di hagadonu hua e made labelaa.   
\c 3  
\s1 Tolole o tangada  
\p
\v 1 Ogu duaahina nei, e dogologo i goodou hagalee hai gii hai digau agoago, idimaa, goodou gu iloo bolo gimaadou digau agoago le e kae di hagi aga damana i digau ala i golo.  
\v 2 Gidaadou huogodoo e hai di hala i nia madagoaa e logo. Maa tangada hagalee hala ana helekai, ia e donu, e mee di benebene dono huaidina hagatau.  
\v 3 Gidaadou e wanga di baalanga gi di ngudu di hoodo bolo gi hagalongo a mee gii hana gi di gowaa belee dagi ginai.  
\v 4 Goodou gi maanadu ina labelaa di hai o di wagabaalii damana dela e hahaangi go di madangi maaloo. Di wagabaalii deenei e mee hua di ulungi go tamaa hoe hua dulii, gei di maa gaa dele gi di gowaa dela e hiihai ginai di gaabinu.  
\v 5 E hai gadoo be tolole tangada, tama dudaginga dulii loo, gei e mee di helekai hagaamu ia i nia hagadilinga mee llauehe.  
\p Maanadua labelaa lodo henua hagatau e mee di dudu go di mada gologolo dulii loo.  
\v 6 Tadau holole le e hai be di ulaula o di ahi. E honu nia hagadilinga huaidu huogodoo, e haga ihala tadau huaidina hagatau, gaa hidi ai tadau mouli, gaa wele i di ahi dela e hanimoi i di ahi dee odi.  
\v 7 Tangada e mee di haga gaidala nia manu, gu haga gaidala nia hagadilinga manu huogodoo ala i henuailala: nia manu lodo geinga, nia manu mamaangi, nia manu dolodolo, mono iga.  
\v 8 Tangada ne haga gaidala dono holole ai. Tolole o tangada le e huaidu huoloo, ge e hagadau dangada, ge e honu i nia mee haga huaidu dangada.  
\v 9 Gidaadou e hai hegau gi tadau holole e danggee gi tadau Dagi mo tadau Damana, gei e hai hegau labelaa i tadau haga halauwa nia daangada ala ne hai i di ada o God.\x * \xo 3.9 \xt Genesis 1.26\x*  
\v 10 Nnelekai danggee mo haga halauwa, le e loomoi hua i di ngudu e dahi. Ogu duaahina nei, nia mee beenei hagalee belee hai.  
\v 11 Di monowai e deemee di hali mai nia wai maangala mono wai mmala.  
\v 12 Ogu duaahina nei, di laagau ‘fig’ e deemee di huwa ono huwa olib, mo di laagau ‘grape’ e deemee labelaa di huwa ono huwa ‘fig’, di monowai mmala e deemee di uwa aga nia wai maangala.   
\s1 Di iloo mee mai i nua  
\p
\v 13 Koai e kabemee, ge iloo i godou baahi? Tangada deelaa le e mee di haga modongoohia dono kabemee mai dono mouli, hegau humalia, mai di manawa hila gi lala mo di iloo.  
\v 14 Maa tubua, hagadugina mo tumaanga la i godou lodo, malaa, goodou hudee heia di huaidu e hai baahi gi di tonu i godou hagaamu godou kabemee.  
\v 15 Di kabemee beenei hagalee ne haneia i di langi. Di mee hua ni henuailala, hagalee di mee ni di Hagataalunga, di mee hua ni Setan.  
\v 16 Di gowaa dela iai tubua mo tumaanga, deenei di gowaa e noho di hinihini mo nia huaidu huogodoo.  
\v 17 Gei di kabemee mai nua, le e madammaa i mua nia mee huogodoo, e noho i di aumaalia, dumaalia ge hila gi lala, gei e honu i tumaalia, gaa hidi ai nia hegau humalia e logowaahee, hagalee dugu gee nia daangada, ge hagalee hai hegau ngudu golomada.  
\v 18 Di humalia deenei la go nia huwa o nia hegau humalia o digau ala e hagahumalia mehanga daangada, ala e dogi nadau lii i di aumaalia.   
\c 4  
\s1 Hai hoo gi henuailala  
\p
\v 1 Nia hagadilinga heheebagi mono lagalagamaaloo huogodoo ala e hai i godou mehanga, le e daamada mai i hee? Ne daamada mai i godou manawa hiihai huaidu ala e hagadau heheebagi i godou lodo i nia madagoaa huogodoo.  
\v 2 Goodou e hiihai gi nia mee, gei goodou e deemee di hai mee ginai, gaa hidi ai goodou e dadaaligi dangada. Goodou e hiihai maaloo gi nia mee, gei goodou e deemee di hai mee ginai, gei goodou ga lagalagamaaloo ga heheebagi. Gei goodou e deemee di hai mee gi di mee e hiihai ginai, idimaa, goodou hagalee tangi ang gi God.  
\v 3 Goodou ga dangidangi gi God, gei goodou hagalee hai mee ginai, idimaa, godou hagamaanadu la hagalee donu, goodou e tangi hua i nia mee e haga manawa lamalia hua goodou.  
\v 4 Goodou digau e de manawa dahi. Goodou e de iloo bolo maa goodou gaa hai nia hoo ni henuailala, dono hadinga bolo goodou nia hagadaumee ni God? Tangada dela e hiihai e hai di hoo hagaaloho ni henuailala, dela go mee gaa hai di hagadaumee ni God.  
\v 5 Goodou hudee maanadu bolo ma di tonu i lodo nia helekai di Beebaa Dabu ai, dela e helekai,  
\q1 “Di hagataalunga ne dugu go God i tadau lodo,  
\q1 le e honu i nia maanadu dubua.”   
\m
\v 6 Tumaalia o God dela e gaamai dehuia gi gidaadou, la koia e damanaiee, gii hai be nnelekai di Beebaa Dabu,  
\q1 “God e huli gi daha mo digau hagamuamua,  
\q1 ge Ia e wanga dono dumaalia gi digau ala e hila gi lala.”\x * \xo 4.6  \xt Proverbs 3.34 \x*   
\m
\v 7 Dugu anga goodou gi God. Hai baahi gi Setan, gei mee gaa lele gi daha mo goodou.  
\v 8 Lloomoi hagahoohoo ina goodou gi baahi o God, gei Mee ga hagahoohoo ia adu gi godou baahi. Digau huaidu, haga madammaa ina godou lima. Digau hai hegau ngudu golomada, haga madammaa ina godou lodo.  
\v 9 Goodou gi manawa gee, tangitangi mo di wawwawe. Huluhia godou gadagada gi di tangi, di godou tenetene gi di manawa gee.  
\v 10 Dugu ina goodou gi lala i mua o God, gei Mee ga haga menege aga goodou.   
\s1 Hudee hagi aga ina godou duaahina dama a Christ  
\p
\v 11 Ogu duaahina nei, goodou hudee hagadau helekai huaidu i godou mehanga. Tangada dela e hagahuaidu be e hagi aga dono duaahina, geia e helekai huaidu mo di hagi aga nnaganoho. Maa goe e hagi aga nnaganoho, gei goe hagalee hagalongo gi nia maa, e hagi aga hua nia maa.  
\v 12 Ma go God hua dela e hai nnaganoho ge e hagi aga tangada. Go Mee hua dela e mee di haga mouli ge e haga halauwa. Goe koai dela bolo goe e hagi aga do duaahina dama a Christ?   
\s1 Hudee bida hagaamu  
\p
\v 13 Hagalongo mai, goodou ala e helekai, “Dangi nei be daiaa gei gimaadou e hula gi di waahale deelaa, gaa noho i golo i di ngadau e dahi, malaa, gimaadou ga huihui gi daha madau mee, ga gila mai tagabae bahihadu.”\x * \xo 4.13  \xt Proverbs 27.1\x*  
\v 14 Gei goodou e de iloo be godou mouli la gaa hai behee i nia laangi ala e lloomoi, idimaa, goodou e hai gadoo be di magalillili o lala di langi, dela hua e gila aga tama madagoaa dulii, ga limalima hua dono hagalee.  
\v 15 Deenei di godou helekai belee hai, “Maa Dimaadua ga dumaalia mai, gei gidaadou ga mouli, gaa hai nia mee aanei be nia mee aalaa.”  
\v 16 Dolomeenei, gei goodou e hagamuamua ge e hagaamu goodou, di hai deenei le e hai gee.  
\v 17 Malaa, tangada dela e iloo ia di mee donu dela belee hai, geia hagalee hai di maa, ia guu hai di hala.   
\c 5  
\s1 Di hagailoo hagalliga gi digau maluagina  
\p
\v 1 Goodou ala e maluagina, hagalongo mai dolomeenei! Goodou gi tangitangi ge gi manawa gee, i di haadanga balua la ga dae adu gi goodou.  
\v 2 Godou maluagina la ga mooho, godou gahu la gaa gai go hiingodo.\x * \xo 5.2  \xt Matthew 6.19\x*  
\v 3 Godou goolo mono silber la gaa tomo. Nia tomo aanei la di haga modongoohia e hai baahi adu gi goodou, gei e gai godou huaidina gadoo be di ahi. Goodou ne benebene godou maluagina i nia laangi hagaodi aanei.  
\v 4 Goodou digi huina nia daangada ala nogo ngalua i lodo godou hadagee. Goodou gi hagalongo gi nadau dee donu. Nia lee o digau e hagabudu godou huwa laagau la gu hagalongo ginai a God, go Tagi Aamua.\x * \xo 5.4  \xt Deuteronomy 24.14-15\x*  
\v 5 Godou mouli i henuailala e honu i di mouli mo di tene balumee. Goodou guu hai goodou gii pedi ang gi di laangi o taaligi.  
\v 6 Goodou gu hagahuaidu, gu daaligi digau nadau ihala ai gii mmade, gei digaula digi hai baahi adu gi goodou.   
\s1 Di manawa hagakono mo talodalo  
\p
\v 7 Ogu duaahina nei, goodou gi manawa hagakono gaa dae loo gi di hanimoi o Tagi. Goodou mmada gi tangada hai hadagee i dono manawa hagakono i dono talitali nia huwa humalia o dana hadagee, gei e manawa hagakono i dono talitali maalia di madagoaa e doo di uwa.  
\v 8 Goodou gi manawa hagakono gi haga damana ina di godou hagadagadagagee, idimaa, di laangi o Tagi la gu hoohoo mai.   
\p
\v 9 Ogu duaahina nei, goodou hudee hagahuaidu ina tangada nei mo tangada nei i godou mehanga, gi de hagi aga hua goodou go God. Goodou gi iloo bolo Tangada hagi aga gu hoohoo mai dono hanimoi.   
\p
\v 10 Ogu duaahina nei, goodou gi langahia nia soukohp ala nogo hai nadau agoago i di ingoo o Tagi. Goodou gii kawe i nadau manawa hagakono mo nadau hagamahi i lodo nadau hagaduadua.  
\v 11 Gidaadou e hai bolo digaula gu maluagina i nadau manawa hagakono i lodo nadau hagaduadua. Goodou gu longono di hai o Job i dono manawa hagakono, gei gu modongoohia di hai o Dimaadua dela gu hagahumalia a mee i di hagaodi gi muli, idimaa, Dimaadua e honu i di aloho mo tumaalia.\x * \xo 5.11  \xt Job 1.21-22; 2.10; Pisalem 103.8\x*   
\p
\v 12 Ogu duaahina nei, i mua nia mee huogodoo, goodou hudee hai hagamodu ma gaa hai godou hagababa. Goodou hudee hai hagamodu gi di langi be gi henuailala, be tei aha e de hilihili. Goodou helekai hua boloo, “Uaa” maa goodou gaa donu, ge “Deeai” maa goodou ga hagalee donu, gi dee too hua goodou gi lodo di hagi aga a God.\x * \xo 5.12  \xt Matthew 5.34-37\x*   
\p
\v 13 Maa tangada i godou baahi gu manawa gee, ia gi dalodalo. Maa iai tangada e tenetene, ia gi daahili hagaamu.  
\v 14 Maa iai tangada i godou baahi e magi, geia gi gahia mai nia daangada mmaadua daumaha, e dalodalo, ge e hagatulu a mee gi di lolo hagalabagau i di ingoo o Tagi.\x * \xo 5.14  \xt Mark 6.13\x*  
\v 15 Talodalo dela e hai aga i lodo di hagadonu, gei tangada magi la gaa hili. Tagi ga hagamaaloo aga a mee, ga dumaalia gi ono hala.  
\v 16 Malaa, goodou gi hagadau hagi aga godou huaidu mo di dalodalo i tangada nei mo tangada nei, gi maaloo goodou. Talodalo o tangada humalia la koia e mogobuna.  
\v 17 Elijah tangada gadoo be gidaadou, mee ne dalodalo hagamahi bolo di uwa gi hudee doo. I nia ngadau e dolu mo di baahi, gei di uwa digi doo.\x * \xo 5.17  \xt 1-Kings 17.1; 18.1\x*  
\v 18 Geia ga dalodalo labelaa, gei di langi gu haga doo dana uwa gi henuailala, gu haga tomo aga nia hagadili.\x * \xo 5.18  \xt 1-Kings 18.42-45\x*   
\p
\v 19 Ogu duaahina nei, maa tangada i godou baahi guu hana gee mo di tonu, goodou heia a mee gii huli hoou labelaa.  
\v 20 Goodou gi langahia bolo tangada dela ma gaa huli tangada huaidu gi daha mo ono hala, ia ne daa di mouli o maa gi daha mo di made, guu gahu nia hala e logo gi tumaalia o nia hala logowaahee.\x * \xo 5.20  \xt Proverbs 10.12; 1-Peter 4.8\x*   